# Automatic Question Generation — Build Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A complete **Automatic Question Generation (AQG)** system from textbooks without LLMs, using the SQuAD 2.0 dataset. The system has two main components:

### 1. Python NLP Engine (`nlp_engine/`)

| Module | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [dataset.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/dataset.py) | SQuAD 2.0 loader — extracts QA pairs, contexts, and stats |
| [preprocessor.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/preprocessor.py) | spaCy NLP pipeline — POS tagging, NER, dependency parsing |
| [answer_extractor.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/answer_extractor.py) | Extracts answer candidates via NER, noun phrases, numbers |
| [question_generator.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/question_generator.py) | Rule-based + template-based question generation with subject-auxiliary inversion |
| [question_ranker.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/question_ranker.py) | 7-feature quality scoring and ranking |
| [difficulty.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/difficulty.py) | 🔥 **Innovation #1** — Easy/Medium/Hard classifier |
| [blooms_taxonomy.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/blooms_taxonomy.py) | 🔥 **Innovation #2** — Bloom's Taxonomy categorization |
| [evaluator.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/nlp_engine/evaluator.py) | BLEU-2 & ROUGE evaluation against SQuAD ground truth |

### 2. Flask API ([app.py](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/app.py))

6 REST endpoints on port 5001: `/api/generate`, `/api/quiz` (🔥 **Innovation #3**), `/api/evaluate`, `/api/stats`, `/api/sample`, `/api/health`

### 3. Next.js Frontend (`web/`)

| Page | Description |
|---|---|
| [/ (Generate)](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/web/src/app/page.tsx) | Text input → question generation with difficulty badges, Bloom's labels, stats bar |
| [/quiz](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/web/src/app/quiz/page.tsx) | Interactive quiz with timer, hints, scoring, answer review |
| [/analysis](file:///Users/taranjain/Documents/vs%20docs/nlp_project/web/src/app/analysis/page.tsx) | Dataset stats, BLEU/ROUGE charts, distribution visualizations |

---

## Verification Results

### ✅ NLP Pipeline Test
```
Raw generated: 20 questions
After filtering: 20 questions
After ranking: 10 questions

Sample output:
1. [EASY  ] [Remember] Who was born in Ulm, Germany in 1879?  → Albert Einstein
2. [MEDIUM] [Remember] Who received the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1921?  → Einstein
3. [MEDIUM] [Remember] What did Einstein receive in 1921?  → the Nobel Prize in Physics
```

### ✅ Flask API Test
- Health check: `{"status": "ok", "service": "AQG Engine"}`
- Generate endpoint: Returns JSON with questions, difficulty, Bloom's level, confidence

### ✅ Next.js Build
- All 3 routes compiled and generated successfully (0 errors)

---

## How to Run

```bash
# Terminal 1: Flask API
cd "/Users/taranjain/Documents/vs docs/nlp_project"
source venv/bin/activate
python app.py

# Terminal 2: Next.js Frontend
cd "/Users/taranjain/Documents/vs docs/nlp_project/web"
npm run dev

# Open http://localhost:3000
```

## Run Evaluation
```bash
source venv/bin/activate
python -m nlp_engine.evaluator --sample 50 --split dev
```
